</li><li><strong>Studiengebühren einführen </strong>to introduce tuition fees
</li><li><strong>Studiengebühren abschaffen </strong>to abolish tuition fees
</li><li><strong>über viel / wenig Geld verfügen </strong>to have a lot of money / a little money
</li><li><strong>mit wenig Geld über die Runden kommen </strong>to make ends meet with a little money
</li><li><strong>in dieser Lebensphase </strong>in this phase of life
</li><li><strong>die Mieten steigen </strong>the rents are rising
</li><li><strong>die Lebenskosten steigen </strong>the cost of living is rising
</li><li><strong>eine günstige Option </strong>a cheap option
</li><li><strong>das WG-Zimmer </strong>the room in a shared flat
</li><li><strong>Das war vielleicht früher so. </strong>That may have been the case in the past.
</li><li><strong>Ich komme zu dem Schluss, dass XY. </strong>I come to the conclusion that XY.
</li><li><strong>Ich finde, dass XY. </strong>I find that XY.
</li><li><strong>Meiner Meinung nach XY. </strong>In my opinion XY.
</li><li><strong>Meines Erachtens XY. </strong>In my opinion XY.
</li><li><strong>Ich finde es problematisch, dass XY. </strong>I find it problematic that XY.
